Short term goals:
- The return of Fast Extension aka 'Fast Peers'
  + Currently incomplete and untested
  + See http://www.bittorrent.org/fast_extensions.html
- Bugs
  + Cannot remove torrents that have open handles (I'm lazy)
  + mkpath for Unicode?
- Protect tracker data from ******* users (See [id://639021]?)
- UDP trackers
  + See http://xbtt.sourceforge.net/udp_tracker_protocol.html
- [cpan://Alter] for objects?
  + How to prevent someone from doing...
    C<{package Net:[...]:Session;my$hack=ego$session;$hack->{q[uploaded]}=9**9}>

Long term goals:
- Internal bans for 'bad' peers
  + Penalty (and eventual ban) for peers who always seem involved
    with bad pieces
  + Penalty for apparent leeches
- limit number of unchoked peers
- optimistic unchoking
- untaint w/ brains
- Disconnect when both are seeds
- improve file handling
  + .piece file to store incoming (sub-)pieces
- Limits for transfer bandwidth (low priority)
- Extensions
  + DHT/PEX (low priority)
      See http://www.bittorrent.org/Draft_DHT_protocol.html
  + Wire protocol encryption (very low priority)
      See http://www.azureuswiki.com/index.php/Message_Stream_Encryption
  + Extension protocol (high priority)
      See http://www.rasterbar.com/products/libtorrent/extension_protocol.html
  + Extension Negotiation Protocol (high priority)
      See http://www.azureuswiki.com/index.php/Extension_negotiation_protocol
  + BitComet Extension Protocol (low priority)
      Currently undocumented. Hmmm... Wireshark to the rescue. :|

